name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: I want to thank & congratulate @JoeDSports on a long and successful career in broadcast journalism. From his first radio job in 1978 at WLIS-AM, to his work at WPOP-AM, & WTIC, he consistently delivered CT with outstanding sports & government policy coverage and I wish him well.

tweet: Consider saving for your child's future education expenses by opening up a @CHET529 account. Tomorrow, 12/29 is the deadline for opening up an account that would be included in your 2020 tax returns. #Startnow #FinancialPlanning. Learn more, here:  https://t.co/3J43LOLQpT

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: During this year's holiday season consider giving the gift of education by opening a @chet529 college savings account for a loved one. Click the link to learn how:  https://t.co/wsj8fFWzNg

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: ICYMI: Listen to my conversation w/ @ctcapitolreport on @WTNH. We discussed how recent studies indicate widespread reluctance among many communities of color to receive the vaccine, and how Black & Brown leaders in CT can help reduce the level of mistrust.  https://t.co/kPMlOtY0YN

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: I believe it is critical for leaders in communities of color to demonstrate, in our actions, that the vaccine is safe and effective. By working together & leading by example, we can reduce the level of mistrust of the vaccine, promote its usage and save lives.

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: The Greater Hartford area has been recognized for its climate leadership! Congrats to @TownofWestHrtfd & @ShariMayor on winning top honors today at the 14th Annual Climate Protection Award competition, & congrats to @MayorBronin for an Honorable mention.    https://t.co/4j5axGPiBx

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: ICYMI: I understand why communities of color may be skeptical of the vaccine w/ our nation’s history of racism combined with racial health disparities. However, I trust the science - the vaccine is the most powerful tool we have to protect our health.  https://t.co/ewFY8WnQUd

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: Congrats to @RepDebHaaland - nominated by @JoeBiden to lead the Department of the Interior. The country's first Native American Cabinet secretary will be a fierce advocate for environmental issues & protect our national parks, wildlife refuges & more.  https://t.co/bSL9vCoTsP

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: And I am urging other Black and Brown leaders across our state to join me and roll up their sleeve to do the same. By working together and leading by example, we can reduce the level of mistrust of the vaccine, promote its usage and save lives. (3/3)

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: That's why, in addition to educating the public on the effectiveness & safety of the vaccine - when the vaccine becomes available, I plan to take it publicly, on camera. See my full statement, here:  https://t.co/xCKqomlbs6 (2/3)

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: Research shows that many people are skeptical of taking the COVID-19 #vaccine, particularly, communities of color. While I understand where their hesitation may stem from- I also believe the vaccine is the most powerful tool we have to protect our family & friends.  (1/3)  https://t.co/MrJPmnJuUs

name: CT Treasurer Shawn T. Wooden
tweet: Thank you, @GovNedLamont. Today, December 14, 2020, is the 8th anniversary of the tragic day when CT lost 20 children and 6 adults to senseless gun violence. We remember the lives of those we lost and hold each of them & their loved ones - deep in our hearts. #SandyHook
